1. Monochromatic: Use Just One Color from the Color Wheel. We can create variations using saturation and value.

2. Complementary Color: Two opposite side color (like yellow and purple)
   
3. Split Complementary: Different Colors with Same Brightness.

4. Analogous Color: Next to Each Other.

5. Triadic: Three Colors in evenly spaced.

6. Tetradic: Two sides of complementary colors and forms rectangle on color wheel.

Color Contrast Ratio(Difference in light between foreground and background): The Higher the Ratio, Easier to Read
1. Never Use Pure White and Black
2. Never Use Hight Foreground on High Background
3. Always Check on Dark Mode Also